column1: Write a JUnit test method for the Java method described below. The test method should have proper and relevant assert statements and avoid repetition of assert statements.

Method: getSecondLevelType Description: /** * @return the raw type unwrapped of the second level of array. * If the object is (single-dimensional or multi-dimensional) array, it is the class of the * elements of the array. For example, this method returns Foo.class for Foo[]. * It will return Foo[].class for Foo[][]. For Foo<String>[][] types, it will return the * type representing Foo<String>[] * (i.e. new TypeToken[]>() {}.getType()). */
